00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:32.000
 with the seeing those very concrete things, and gross things,

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:39.000
 and then the more you experience that compassion, the more fine-tuned your perception can be.

00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:41.000
 And then, you know, exactly that progression is.

00:33:41.000 --> 00:33:45.000
 You see the gross suffering, you know, when it comes to its full fruition,

00:33:45.000 --> 00:33:47.000
 then you see what's causing it.

00:33:47.000 --> 00:33:51.000
 And then you realize that, you know, your compassion doesn't have to be sparked by something,

00:33:51.000 --> 00:33:54.000
 but it's continually within awareness.

00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:57.000
 It's really quite beautiful, very profound.

00:33:57.000 --> 00:34:00.000
 There's no corner in samsara that's happy.

00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:05.000
 Notice there are three types of suffering, the suffering of suffering, suffering of change,

00:34:05.000 --> 00:34:07.000
 and all-pervasive suffering.

00:34:07.000 --> 00:34:12.000
 The very nature of everything coming together is it's constantly uncertain.

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:14.000
 It always is going to break.

00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:21.000
 Like literally, there's nothing we ever do in the samsara framework that's happy.

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:25.000
 It's always plagued with instability.

00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:29.000
 And then really, I think if we get sensitive to that, then the compassion starts really coming

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:29.000
 strong,

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:36.000
 and that's really too when more of this also like sinking into this emptiness

00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:40.000
 or more flexible, open aspects of compassion is important too.

00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:43.000
 Because we can't just be overly sensitive and really will kind of drown

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:48.000
 in the sensitivity to the amazing suffering that's always happening.

00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:52.830
 But I think really this is, I mean, two things I thought, and the story is that if we look at a san

00:34:52.830 --> 00:34:53.000
gha,

