 And it's really this view or that motivation in terms of Vajrayana context, like you said,

00:35:24.000 --> 00:35:29.000
 called the aspiration, so-called Hinayana aspiration, just my own freedom from suffering,

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:33.000
 or freedom of all beings from their suffering, the Mahayana aspiration.

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:35.000
 It just comes down to a view.

00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:40.000
 We can do so much work, put in so much time, and that view is really critical.

00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:45.000
 Both the philosophical way we orient and the heartfelt way that we really feel

00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:47.000
 and activate ourselves in that.

00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:52.000
 Because 12 years, obviously he's purifying and accumulating merit,

00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:55.000
 but it really comes down to the view in the end.

00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:58.000
 And so it says how we start, we really should look at how we start.

00:35:58.000 --> 00:36:01.000
 And at the same point, the second thing that was really strong,

00:36:01.000 --> 00:36:07.000
 as this is a teaching we hear every time, it's such a fundamental, basic, essential,

00:36:07.000 --> 00:36:12.000
 can't do anything without this teaching in Buddhism topic.

